    CallableMethod

    public class ExternalMethodDeclaration
extends MethodDeclaration
    MethodDeclaration extension that represents the declaration of an external method node type. See decodeStatement(Node, String, Location, boolean) for more details on what correct inputs look like.
    Since:

      • decodeStatement

        public static ExternalMethodDeclaration decodeStatement(Node parent,
                                                        java.lang.String statement,
                                                        Location location,
                                                        boolean require)
        Decode the given statement into a ExternalMethodDeclaration instance, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null.
        Example inputs include:
        • external int getAge(String name, int age)
        • external int calculateArea(int width, int height)
        • external void doNothing() as pointlessFunction
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent node of the statement.
        statement - The statement to try to decode into a ExternalMethodDeclaration instance.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a Method.

      • interactWord

        public void interactWord(java.lang.String word,
                         int wordNumber,
                         Bounds bounds,
                         int numWords,
                         java.lang.String leftDelimiter,
                         java.lang.String rightDelimiter,
                         Node.ExtraData extra)
        Description copied from class: Node
        Method that is to be overridden. Whenever the iterateWords(String) method is called, this method will be called with the specific word and the number (order) the word came in the statement.
        Overrides:
        interactWord in class Node
        Parameters:
        word - The word that was found.
        wordNumber - The index of the word on a word-by-word basis.
        bounds - The bounds of the word that was found.
        numWords - The number of words that were parsed.
        leftDelimiter - The text that is between the previous word and the current word.
        rightDelimiter - The text that is between the current word and the next word.
        extra - The extra data that may or may not be needed for the interactWord() methods.
        See Also:
        Node.interactWord(java.lang.String, int, net.fathomsoft.nova.util.Bounds, int, java.lang.String, java.lang.String, net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.Node.ExtraData)
